
                                            Social development officials are appealing for information to track the parents of an abandoned baby found dead and frozen in Lwandle.
                                         CAPE TOWN - The frozen body of a three-month-old baby has been discovered in a dustbin in Lwandle  in Strand. Western Cape Social Development says it’s supporting a police investigation. Social development officials are appealing for information to track the parents of an abandoned baby found dead and frozen in Lwandle. Social workers are also on standby to assist. The department's Sihle Ngobese said: “Most disturbingly the corpse was found concealed in black plastic bags and was frozen. We condemn this brutal incident in the strongest, strongest terms possible." At the same time, a three-day-old baby was found in a field in Kwadwesi, in the Eastern Cape.